# Wireframe Specification

## Required Wireframe Screens

Each group must create the following minimum wireframes and export each screen as PNG.

| Wireframe File | Purpose | Minimum Elements to Show | Related Requirements |
|---|---|---|---|
| /wireframes/homepage.png | Entry point of the system | Smart Campus Event Hub title, target users (students, staff, organizers), purpose of the platform, featured/upcoming events, main action buttons (Browse Events, Register, Login), navigation menu | FR-01, FR-02 |
| /wireframes/event-registration.png | User event registration | Event details, registration form (Name, Student ID, Email, Faculty), required fields, Register button, Cancel button, validation/error messages, confirmation area | FR-03, FR-10, FR-11 |
| /wireframes/event-list.png | List available campus events | Event cards/table, event category, event status, date, location, organizer, Search bar, Filter by category/date/status, View Details/Register buttons | FR-05, FR-06, FR-08 |
| /wireframes/event-detail.png | Show selected event | Event title, description, category, organizer, venue, schedule, available seats, registration status, Register button, Back button | FR-07, FR-08 |
| /wireframes/dashboard.png | Summary/analytics view | Total events, upcoming events, registered users, completed events, popular categories, attendance summary, simple chart/cards | FR-12 |
| /wireframes/admin-dashboard.png | Admin event management | Event management table, Add Event, Edit Event, Delete Event, Approve/Reject Event, Update Status, Manage Registrations, Search and Filter | FR-09, FR-08 |

## Wireframe Quality Rules

- Use consistent navigation, colors, typography, and labels across all screens.
- Avoid decorative-only screens with no functional meaning.
- Show realistic sample event data instead of empty placeholders.
- Every screen must connect directly to the final prototype requirements.
- Include interactive elements such as search, filter, registration, status updates, and confirmation messages.
- Wireframes may be created using Figma, Canva, PowerPoint, HTML/CSS, or another suitable prototyping tool.
- Ensure the design is responsive for both desktop and mobile devices.
